That is a good point @jfuss. I missed layers in the first PR, and this one will cover that too. And the root cause is coming from pass-by-reference. This `env_vars` dictionary is altered in the way below which changes the `build_definition` signature which causes re-builds for cached build.

But instead of `deepcopy`'ing in different places, we can think about moving `env_vars` property of [`FunctionBuildDefinition`](https://github.com/aws/aws-sam-cli/blob/develop/samcli/lib/build/build_graph.py#L406) and [`LayerBuildDefinition`](https://github.com/aws/aws-sam-cli/blob/develop/samcli/lib/build/build_graph.py#L350) into [`AbstractBuildDefinition`](https://github.com/aws/aws-sam-cli/blob/develop/samcli/lib/build/build_graph.py#L320) and then add a property method which will return the copied instance of dictionary.

```
class AbstractBuildDefinition:
    """
    Abstract class for build definition
    Build definition holds information about each unique build
    """

    def __init__(self, source_md5: str, env_vars: Optional[Dict] = None) -> None:
        self.uuid = str(uuid4())
        self.source_md5 = source_md5
        self._env_vars = env_vars if env_vars else {}

    @property
    def env_vars(self):
        return deepcopy(self._env_vars)
```

